headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 22 points, including a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 32.1 seconds left, and the Detroit Pistons rallied to beat the Charlotte Hornets 118-112 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey hits late 3-pointer to help Pistons beat Hornets 118-112

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 21 points against his former team and the Indiana Pacers beat the Sacramento Kings 107-104 on Friday night to stop a four-game losing streak.

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 20 of his 33 points in the third quarter and the Portland Trail Blazers erased a 20-point deficit, snapping Washington's six-game winning streak Friday night with a 124-116 victory over the Wizards.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers rally from 20 down to end Wizards' win streak

headlines.description: — Devin Booker wore a hockey toque to deal with the sub-zero temperatures in Boston and pulled out a baseball metaphor to describe his possible return to the basketball court.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 25, leads Suns to 106-94 win over Celtics

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 32 points, Gary Trent Jr. added 29 and the Toronto Raptors snapped a two-game skid with a 117-111 win over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has 32 as Raptors get 117-111 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 20 points and fellow reserve Moritz Wagner scored 19 as Orlando’s bench propelled the Magic to a 127-120 win against the Minnesota Timberwolves that included a <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Wolves 127-120 after fight, 5 players ejected

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 33 points and 10 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers beat San Antonio 137-125 on Friday night, sending the scuffling Spurs to their eighth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's double-double keys 76ers as Spurs drop 8th straight

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 27 points and six assists to lead the Atlanta Hawks to a 115-108 victory over the Utah Jazz on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 27 to lead Hawks past Jazz, 115-108
